ng Functions Were Derived from the Wright–Guild Data". <i>Color Research and Application</i> <b>23</b> (4): 259. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<span class="neverexpand"><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1002%2F%28SICI%291520-6378%28199808%2923%3A4%3C259%3A%3AAID-COL18%3E3.0.CO%3B2-7" class="external text" title="http://dx.doi.org/10.1002%2F%28SICI%291520-6378%28199808%2923%3A4%3C259%3A%3AAID-COL18%3E3.0.CO%3B2-7" rel="nofollow">10.1002/(SICI)1520-6378(199808)23:4&lt;259::AID-COL18&gt;3.0.CO;2-7</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Erratum%3A+How+the+CIE+1931+Color-Matching+Functions+Were+Derived+from+the+Wright%E2%80%93Guild+Data&amp;rft.jtitle=Color+Research+and++Application&amp;rft.aulast=Fairman+H.S.%2C+Brill+M.H.%2C+Hemmendinger+H.&amp;rft.au=Fairman+H.S.%2C+Brill+M.H.%2C+Hemmendinger+H.&amp;rft.date=August+1998&amp;rft.volume=23&amp;rft.issue=4&amp;rft.pages=259&amp;rft_id=info:doi/10.1002%2F%28SICI%291520-6378%28199808%2923%3A4%3C259%3A%3AAID-COL18%3E3.0.CO%3B2-7&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:CIE_1931_color_space"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-10"><b><a href="#cite_ref-10" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFCIE1926">CIE (1926). <i>Commission internationale de l'Eclairage proceedings, 1924</i>. Cambridge University Press, Cambridge.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Commission+internationale+de+l%27Eclairage+proceedings%2C+1924&amp;rft.aulast=CIE&amp;rft.au=CIE&amp;rft.date=1926&amp;rft.pub=Cambridge+University+Press%2C+Cambridge&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:CIE_1931_color_space"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> Note that the 1924 luminous efficiency function seriously underestimates sensitivity at wavelengths below 460 nm, and has been supplemented with newer and more accurate luminosity curves; see <a href="/wiki/Luminosity_function#Improvements_to_the_standard" title="Luminosity function">Luminosity function#Improvements to the standard</a>.</li>
</ol>
</div>
<p><a name="Further_reading" id="Further_reading"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=CIE_1931_color_space&amp;action=edit&amp;section=11" title="Edit section: Further reading">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Further reading</span></h2>
<ul>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFBroadbent2004">Broadbent, Arthur D. (August 2004). "A critical review of the development of the CIE1931 RGB color-matching functions". <i>Color Research &amp; Applications</i> <b>29</b> (4): 267–272. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<span class="neverexpand"><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1002%2Fcol.20020" class="external text" title="http://dx.doi.org/10.1002%2Fcol.20020" rel="nofollow">10.1002/col.20020</a></span>.  "This article describes the development of the CIE1931 chromaticity coordinates and color-matching functions starting from the initial experimental data of W. D. Wright and J. Guild. Sufficient information is given to allow the reader to reproduce and verify the results obtained at each stage of the calculations and to analyze critically the procedures used. Unfortunately, some of the information required for the coordinate transformations was never published and the appended tables provide likely versions of that missing data.".</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=A+critical+review+of+the+development+of+the+CIE1931+RGB+color-matching+functions&amp;rft.jtitle=Color+Research+%26+Applications&amp;rft.aulast=Broadbent&amp;rft.aufirst=Arthur+D.&amp;rft.au=Broadbent%2C+Arthur+D.&amp;rft.date=August+2004&amp;rft.volume=29&amp;rft.issue=4&amp;rft.pages=267%E2%80%93272&amp;rft_id=info:doi/10.1002%2Fcol.20020&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:CIE_1931_color_space"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFTrezona2001">Trezona, Pat W. (2001). "Derivation of the 1964 CIE 10° XYZ Colour-Matching Functions and Their Applicability in Photometry". <i>Color Research and Application</i> <b>26</b> (1): 67–75. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<span class="neverexpand"><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1002%2F1520-6378%28200102%2926%3A1%3C67%3A%3AAID-COL7%3E3.0.CO%3B2-4" class="external text" title="http://dx.doi.org/10.1002%2F1520-6378%28200102%2926%3A1%3C67%3A%3AAID-COL7%3E3.0.CO%3B2-4" rel="nofollow">10.1002/1520-6378(200102)26:1&lt;67::AID-COL7&gt;3.0.CO;2-4</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Derivation+of+the+1964+CIE+10%C2%B0+XYZ+Colour-Matching+Functions+and+Their+Applicability+in+Photometry&amp;rft.jtitle=Color+Research+and+Application&amp;rft.aulast=Trezona&amp;rft.aufirst=Pat+W.&amp;rft.au=Trezona%2C+Pat+W.&amp;rft.date=2001&amp;rft.volume=26&amp;rft.issue=1&amp;rft.pages=67%E2%80%9375&amp;rft_id=info:doi/10.1002%2F1520-6378%28200102%2926%3A1%3C67%3A%3AAID-COL7%3E3.0.CO%3B2-4&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:CIE_1931_color_space"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFWright2007">Wright, William David (2007). "Golden Jubilee of Colour in the CIE—The Historical and Experimental Background to the 1931 CIE System of Colorimetry". in János Schanda. <i>Colorimetry</i>. Wiley Interscience. pp.&#160;9–24. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<span class="neverexpand"><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1002%2F9780470175637.ch2" class="external text" title="http://dx.doi.org/10.1002%2F9780470175637.ch2" rel="nofollow">10.1002/9780470175637.ch2</a></span>. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780470049044" class="internal">ISBN 9780470049044</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Golden+Jubilee+of+Colour+in+the+CIE%E2%80%94The+Historical+and+Experimental+Background+to+the+1931+CIE+System+of+Colorimetry&amp;rft.atitle=Colorimetry&amp;rft.aulast=Wright&amp;rft.aufirst=William+David&amp;rft.au=Wright%2C+William+David&amp;rft.date=2007&amp;rft.pages=pp.%26nbsp%3B9%E2%80%9324&amp;rft.pub=Wiley+Interscience&amp;rft_id=info:doi/10.1002%2F9780470175637.ch2&amp;rft.isbn=9780470049044&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:CIE_1931_color_space"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> (originally published by the <a href="/wiki/Society_of_Dyers_and_Colourists" title="Society of Dyers and Colourists">Society of Dyers and Colourists</a>, Bradford, 1981.)</li>
</ul>
